import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="Windeatts Solicitors' privacy policy. How we collect, use and protect your personal data."
  breadcrumbs={[{ label: 'Privacy Policy' }]}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <div class="prose prose-lg prose-headings:font-(family-name:--font-heading) prose-headings:text-navy">
      <p>
        Windeatts LLP is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect,
        use and safeguard your personal data in accordance with the UK General Data Protection
        Regulation (UK GDPR) and the Data Protection Act 2018.
      </p>

      <h2>Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Windeatts LLP is the data controller for the personal data we process. We are a Limited
        Liability Partnership registered in England and Wales (OC382943), authorised and regulated
        by the Solicitors Regulation Authority (SRA No. 636433).
      </p>
      <p>
        Our registered office is at 20 Fore Street, Kingsbridge, Devon TQ7 1NY.
      </p>

      <h2>What Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>We may collect and process the following personal data:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name, address, email address and telephone number</li>
        <li>Date of birth and identification documents</li>
        <li>Financial information relevant to your legal matter</li>
        <li>Information about your legal matter, which may include special category data</li>
        <li>Information provided when you contact us through our website</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
      <p>We use your personal data to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Provide legal services to you</li>
        <li>Communicate with you about your matter</li>
        <li>Comply with our legal and regulatory obligations</li>
        <li>Carry out anti-money laundering and identity verification checks</li>
        <li>Manage our business, including accounting and administration</li>
        <li>Send you relevant updates about our services (where you have consented)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Legal Basis for Processing</h2>
      <p>We process your personal data on the following bases:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Contract:</strong> Processing is necessary for the performance of our contract with you to provide legal services</li>
        <li><strong>Legal obligation:</strong> Processing is necessary to comply with our legal and regulatory obligations</li>
        <li><strong>Legitimate interests:</strong> Processing is necessary for our legitimate business interests, such as managing our practice</li>
        <li><strong>Consent:</strong> Where you have given your consent, for example to receive marketing communications</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How Long We Keep Your Data</h2>
      <p>
        We retain your personal data for as long as necessary for the purposes for which it was
        collected. For client files, we typically retain files for a minimum of six years after the
        conclusion of the matter, in line with our professional obligations and limitation periods.
        Some files may be retained for longer where required.
      </p>

      <h2>Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Under the UK GDPR, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Request access to your personal data</li>
        <li>Request correction of inaccurate data</li>
        <li>Request erasure of your data (in certain circumstances)</li>
        <li>Object to or restrict processing of your data</li>
        <li>Request data portability</li>
        <li>Withdraw consent at any time (where processing is based on consent)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        This website uses only essential cookies required for the site to function. We do not
        use tracking cookies or share data with third-party advertising platforms.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have any questions about this privacy policy or wish to exercise your data protection
        rights, please contact us:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Email: <a href="mailto:law@windeatts.co.uk">law@windeatts.co.uk</a></li>
        <li>Telephone: <a href="tel:01548858947">01548 858947</a></li>
        <li>Write to: Windeatts LLP, 20 Fore Street, Kingsbridge, Devon TQ7 1NY</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the Information Commissioner's Office
        (ICO) at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">ico.org.uk</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
